Define Capybara.app for feature specs

When trying to run feature tests using capybara (e.g., `visit "/"`),
I was getting error messages like ...

```
Failure/Error: visit "/"
ArgumentError:
  rack-test requires a rack application, but none was given
```

By assigning `Capybara.app` to an instance of `Sinatra::Application`
in `spec/spec_helper.rb`, I was able to run the feature tests.

Define rake spec task

I ran into an issue with the skeleton when I tried to run my test suite using either `rake spec` or the default rake task.  When I ran the tasks, nothing happened, and it appeared that things failed silently; I was not told that rake didn't know how to build the task 'spec'.

If I ran the test suite with the `rspec` command, the tests ran.

I was able to run the test suite through the rake tasks after defining the spec task in this commit.
